<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A14/355</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Burton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                1925.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 30.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am enclosing a writing
                            signed by the three Delegates who did not join in the signature of the
                            Treaties. This might assume considerable importance and I send it to
                            you.</p>
                        <p>The Conference came to a close at three o’clock today and in reviewing
                            what has been done, I think we have great reason for satisfaction in the
                            results.</p>
                        <p>Very cordially yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore E.
                            Burton</hi></signed></closer>
                        <pb facs="0186" n="60" xml:id="pg_60"/>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</seg></opener>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Statement Approving the Provisions of the
                                    Convention and Consenting to Its Signature</hi></head>
                            <p>The undersigned Delegates, having examined the text of the Convention
                                for the Control of the Trade in Arms, Ammunition and Implements of
                                War, approve of its provisions and consent to the signing thereof by
                                the Chairman and Vice-Chairman of the American Delegation.</p>
                            <closer><signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">A. T. Long</hi></item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Dulles</hi></item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">C. L’H. Ruggles</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                                <lb/>
                                <dateline rendition="#left"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                        1925</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>